<file path=".LLM_INSTRUCTIONS.md">
This a NixOS configuration repository. My whole system is defined here and nowhere else.
If modules or flake inputs aren't used, ignore them, I'll use them in the futur or already used them.
`nh` is used to build, test and switch NixOS configurations. It is normal to find a `nixosModules` field in `flake.nix`.

## Hosts

`Khazad-dum` is a Framework 16" laptop. My main workstation.
`Valinor` is my homelab and my production server.

### `Khazad-dum`
It has 2 graphical environment (both on Wayland), Gnome and Hyprland. It is normal, I want to be able to switch from one to another.

### `Valinor`

Whather is referencing `/mnt/Erebor` is managed by a `docker-compose.yml` file inside the `/mnt/Erebor/War-goats/appdata/docker-compose.yml`. All my services data live here.
`/mnt/Erebor` contains 3 raid `lv` managed by `lvm`. `War-goats` are SSDs in RAID1, `Thorin` are HDDs in RAID5 and `Dain` are HDDs in RAID6.

### Common

Both hosts have custom `iptable` rules. They're destined to allow containers to talk to each other (for some reason, firewall blocks packets on NixOS).
</file>

